        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 3:38PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 337 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Brantley, or near Buena
Vista, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Buena Vista, Talbotton, Junction City, Geneva, Brantley, Juniper,
Baldwinville, Charing, Oakland, Olive Branch, Po Biddy Crossroads,
Mauk, Howard, Tazewell, Marion Estates, and Box Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
